## Site Visits vs Site Visitor Numbers - CRITICAL DISTINCTION

**NEVER confuse these two different elements:**

1. **"Site Visits"** (Above First Footer - Teal Footer):
   - Location: Section above the teal footer (first footer)
   - Text: "Site Visits" (NOT "Site Visitors")
   - HTML class: `.visitor-text` with text "Site Visits"
   - CSS class: `.site-visits` section
   - Purpose: Shows visit count above the enrollment footer

2. **"Site Visitor Numbers"** (Second Footer - Dark Footer):
   - Location: Bottom right of second footer (dark gray footer)
   - Text: "Site Visitor Numbers: [number]" (full phrase)
   - HTML class: `.footer-visitors`
   - CSS: `text-align: right` in `.footer-bottom-line`
   - Purpose: Shows visitor count in footer copyright area

**Rules:**
- "Site Visits" = Above first footer, simple text
- "Site Visitor Numbers" = Second footer bottom right, full phrase
- NEVER use "Site Visitors" anywhere - it doesn't exist
- Copyright in second footer = LEFT aligned
- Site Visitor Numbers in second footer = RIGHT aligned

## CRITICAL: Web View vs Mobile View - Alignment Rules

**NEVER apply mobile responsive styles to web/desktop view:**

### Web View (Desktop) - Default Styles
- **Hero Section**: 
  - `.hero-left`: `align-items: flex-start` (LEFT-aligned)
  - NO `text-align: center` on hero content
  - Content should be left-aligned by default
  
- **Footer First Block (Teal Footer)**:
  - `.footer-content`: `justify-items: start` (NOT center)
  - `.footer-left`: `align-items: flex-start`, `padding-left: 0.75rem` (minimal padding)
  - `.footer-right`: `align-items: flex-start`, `padding-left: 4rem`
  - `.enrollment-benefits li`: `text-align: left` (NOT center)
  - Content should be left/right aligned, NOT centered
  
- **Footer Second Block (Dark Footer)**:
  - `.footer-bottom-line`: `justify-content: space-between`
  - `.footer-copyright`: `text-align: left`
  - `.footer-visitors`: `text-align: right`
  - Copyright LEFT, Site Visitors RIGHT

### Mobile View (max-width: 768px) - Responsive Styles ONLY
- **Hero Section**: 
  - `.hero-left`: `align-items: center`, `text-align: center` (ONLY in mobile breakpoint)
  
- **Footer First Block**:
  - `.footer-left`: `align-items: center`, `text-align: center` (ONLY in mobile breakpoint)
  - `.footer-right`: `align-items: center`, `text-align: center` (ONLY in mobile breakpoint)
  - `.enrollment-benefits li`: `text-align: center` (ONLY in mobile breakpoint)
  
- **Footer Second Block**:
  - `.footer-bottom-line`: `flex-direction: column` (ONLY in mobile breakpoint)
  - Keep left/right alignment even in mobile for copyright/visitors

### Rule Enforcement
- **ALWAYS** check if changes are in a `@media` query before applying
- **NEVER** change default (web) styles to center unless explicitly requested for web view
- **ONLY** apply centering in mobile breakpoints (`@media (max-width: 768px)`)
- **VERIFY** that web view remains left/right aligned after mobile fixes
- **TEST** both web and mobile views after any alignment changes

### Common Mistakes
- ❌ Applying `text-align: center` to web view when only mobile should be centered
- ❌ Changing `align-items: flex-start` to `center` in default styles
- ❌ Modifying `justify-items: start` to `center` in `.footer-content` default
- ❌ Forgetting to wrap mobile-only centering in `@media` queries

